The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Sunday, July 25, 2004 				Metro Recommends
THE VCD 
	(MusicWorld, Rs 199) This 1976 film tracks the plight of Travis Bickle (Robert De Niro), a Vietnam war veteran who drives a cab in New York City. When he meets 12-year-old prostitute Iris (Jodie Foster), Bickle tries to rescue her. Yet another stark and disturbing classic by director Martin Scorcese.THE EVENT
	(Nandan II) The small-screen fare features Koushik Gangulys Chhaya Chhobi on Monday at 6 pm, Dipanjan Basus Simante Dariye at 3 pm and Anjan Dutts Bhalobashar Katha at 6 pm on Thursday. Theres Atanu Ghoshs Amriter Putra at 3 pm on Friday and Arnab Banerjees Tekka at 6 pm on Saturday.THE TOURNEY				 																																	(Ten Sports, July 26, 1.15 am) The title showdown in Lima between arch-rivals Brazil and Argentina promises plenty of fireworks. While Brazil, powered by six-goal hero Adriano, have displayed their depth in reaching thus far minus the stars, Argentina will be banking on new kid Tevezs free-kick prowess to wreak revenge after their recent World Cup qualifier debacle. 

